          "sequence": 28,
          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I've completed the impact analysis for `get_list_filter()` in the Django repository. Here's what I found:\n\n## Summary\n\nI identified **5 files** in the Django codebase that reference `get_list_filter`:\n\n1. **`django/contrib/admin/options.py`** - Contains the definition of `get_list_filter()` method (line 1110) and two call sites (lines 498 and 863)\n\n2. **`tests/modeladmin/tests.py`** - Contains an override of `get_list_filter()` in a test ModelAdmin subclass (line 245)\n\n3. **`tests/admin_changelist/admin.py`** - Contains an override of `get_list_filter()` in a test ModelAdmin subclass `DynamicListFilterChildAdmin` (line 181)\n\n4. **`docs/ref/contrib/admin/index.txt`** - Contains documentation for the `get_list_filter()` method (multiple references)\n\n5. **`docs/releases/1.5.txt`** - Contains release notes mentioning the introduction of `get_list_filter()` in Django 1.5 (line 349)\n\n## Impact Considerations\n\nIf you change the signature of `get_list_filter()`:\n- The **main definition** in `options.py` must be updated\n- The **two call sites** in `options.py` (list view and validation code) may need adjustment\n- Both **test overrides** must be updated to match the new signature\n- **Documentation** should be updated to reflect the new signature\n\nThe submission has been saved to `/workspace/submission.json` as a JSON array of all affected file paths.",
